tuiMatchProduct

public java.lang.String tuiMatchProduct()
Second TUI, if it exists. This TUI is used for matching partial Products objects to full Works objects. Use this value to ensure correct Tui value matching for cases when a video Product GDO contains multiple partial Work GDOs. Each partial Work GDO corresponds to a full Works object, and each full Works object contains the GNSDK_GDO_VALUE_TUI value, incremented by one digit to maintain data integrity with Gracenote Service. The GNSDK_GDO_VALUE_TUI_MATCH_PRODUCT maps the partial Works object Tui value to the full Works object.

The language of a returned object depends on availability. Information in the language set for the locale may not be available, and the object's information may be available only in its default official language. For example, if a locale's set language is Spanish, but the object's information is available only in English, this value returns as English.

reputation

public java.lang.String reputation()
Film's reputation, e.g., "Classic", "Chick Flick", or "Cult". This is a critical or popular "value" that is assigned to a work, usually long after the work was released, though some works may qualify shortly after release (e.g., "instant classic" or "blockbuster release").

Remarks:

This is a list-based value requiring that the list be loaded into memory through a successful call to gnsdk_manager_locale_load.
